{{Infobox tool | name = RepRap Snappy | image = RepRap Snappy 3D printer Version 0.9.jpg | caption = RepRap Snappy 3D printer, Version 0.9 | image2 = RepRap Snappy 3D printer rendering.png | caption2 = RepRap Snappy 3D printer rendering, Version 1.1b | other_name = | classification = [[Fused deposition modeling]] [[3D printer]] | types = | used_with = | inventor = RevarBat | manufacturer = | model = | related = }}
The '''RepRap Snappy''' is an [[Open-source model|open-source]] [[fused deposition modeling]] [[3D printer]], part of the [[RepRap project]], it is the most self replicating 3D printer in the world.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://hackaday.com/2015/09/12/the-most-self-replicating-reprap-yet/|title=The Most Self-Replicating RepRap Yet|last=By|website=Hackaday|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref><ref name="atlasobscura.com">{{Cite web|url=http://www.atlasobscura.com/articles/the-utopian-promise-of-reprap-the-3d-printer-that-can-almost-print-itself|title=The Utopian Promise Of RepRap, the 3D Printer That Can—Almost—Print Itself|date=2016-02-24|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref>
The RepRap Snappy is designed to address the core goal of the RepRap project of creating a '''general-purpose [[Self-replicating machine|self-replicating manufacturing machine]]''<nowiki/>'.<ref name="atlasobscura.com"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://reprap.org/|title=RepRap - RepRapWiki|website=reprap.org|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref> The RepRap Snappy is able to create 73% of its own parts by volume with a design that eliminates as many of the non 3D printed parts as possible including belts and bearings which are replaced with a rack and pinion system.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://3dprintingindustry.com/news/reprap-snappy-is-the-most-3d-printable-3d-printer-yet-57957/|title=RepRap Snappy is the Most 3D Printable 3D Printer Yet|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref> The name Snappy comes from the use of snap fit connectors used on the small printed parts to construct larger pieces, this both cuts down on the use of non 3D printed parts and means a smaller build volume is needed on the machine producing the parts.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /> The only non self replicating parts on the printer are the motors, electronics, a glass build plate and one 686 bearing, the 3D printed parts take around 150 hours to create.<ref name=":1" /> The RepRap Snappy received an honourable mention in the Uplift Prize Grand Personal Manufacturing Prize.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kprize.wordpress.com/prize-specifications/|title=Prize Specifications|date=2010-07-18|language=en-US|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref>
